                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/2060: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Arica</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Von Tresckow</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-03-27T10:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1926—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For Lassiter. Message from Ambassador Collier indicates that Chile is now
                    hesitating about accepting good offices. Under the circumstances it is
                    imperative that you go ahead with registration today, if possible; if not, be
                    prepared to continue at any moment. We shall keep you informed. I am still
                    hopeful that our good offices will be accepted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
